        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl6_Label1"><p>The VMDK is an open file format, created by VMware and mainly used for cloud computing and virtualization services. Basically, the .vmdk files are virtual disks, which contain all the information of a VMware virtual machine. There are different types of .VMDK files, those related to virtual machines on VMware Workstation Player and Virtualbox, which [&hellip;]</p>
